**General rules read off this matrix:**

- **No direct LM → HM** or HM → LM. Everything between minds goes through the Callosum.
- **Athena → Mnemosyne is propose-only.** Commits require HM approval.
- **Auxiliary reads from Mamba state are always `.detach()`.** No gradients flow into the kernel from auxiliaries — including from metacognitive heads.
- **Every external effect crosses ClawGuard.** Reflection trace writes are no exception.
- **Themis observes; Themis does not think.** Themis reads metacognitive head outputs and reflection traces, but only as numbers — never modifying head outputs or having opinions on whether predictions are semantically right.
- **Each mind has its own metacognitive head** — LM’s head reads only LM’s state slice; HM’s head reads only HM’s. Symmetry preserved.
- **Reflection traces always land in Pegasus** (episodic). Durable identity claims from traces escalate through HM as Mnemosyne proposals; never auto-committed.
- **ClawGuard and Themis are matched deterministic regulators** — ClawGuard regulates outside-world boundary (tool calls, files, retrieval, identity proposals); Themis regulates inter-mind boundary (contribution ratio, packet flow, calibration-weighted routing). When future design calls for a “smart regulator,” it should follow one of these two deterministic shapes, not invent a third pattern.

