## 11. v0.5 Build Targets

**Cognitive layer:**

- **LM:** ~50M parameters, hybrid Transformer/Mamba-3, MiMo per-head, 2 of N heads designated identity heads
- **HM:** ~50M parameters, same architecture as LM (equal capacity for Themis)
- **Total cognitive layer:** ~100M

**Per-mind auxiliary heads (gradient-isolated, `.detach()` reads):**

- Metacognitive head (LM and HM, see §3.4) — multi-dim outcome prediction
- Action head (feeds Controller, see §10.4)
- Boundary head (feeds ClawGuard preprocessor, advisory only, see §10.4)
- Gate head (feeds retrieval_gate, advisory only, see §10.4)
- Risk-estimator head (LM and HM, advisory only, see §10.5)

**Memory layer:**

- Pegasus with SRMU-style write gating (§10.2) and xMemory-style hierarchical retrieval (§10.3) operational
- Pegasus messaging gateway (§5.3.1) operational with `RETRIEVAL_INGEST` ClawGuard gating on all inbound content
- Pegasus skills registry (§5.3.2) operational with the LM/HM-propose → Athena-sandbox → HM-review → ClawGuard-`SKILL_REGISTRATION` pipeline
- Pegasus MCP integration (§5.3.3) operational as a protocol adapter, all tool calls gated by ClawGuard
- Mnemosyne with propose/commit/reject discipline operational
- FwPKM stub or first prototype depending on Colab availability
- Reflection-trace pipeline (§3.4.2) writing to Pegasus, both lightweight (every turn) and deep structured (Controller-triggered)

**Safety layer:**

- ClawGuard full pipeline per §10.1 — task-specific rule induction, baseline invariants, per-tool-call interception, skill inspection, allow/deny/ambiguous classification, audit log
- ClawGuard `SKILL_REGISTRATION` boundary operational — two-stage gating with Athena sandbox + HM review preceding ClawGuard validation

**Steam Deck role:** integration-correctness rig. Tests every component connects, no NaNs, gradients flow correctly (and don’t flow where they shouldn’t — auxiliaries detach properly), state saves/loads bit-identically, Controller fires with expected action distribution under locked hard rules, memory writes pass SRMU gates, ClawGuard blocks what it should, Themis maintains LM/HM ratio, Callosum routes packets correctly, Pegasus stores and retrieves without crossing into “thinking,” Mnemosyne propose/commit/reject works, Athena’s proposals are evaluated by HM, metacognitive heads produce calibrated outputs and trace writes roundtrip cleanly through SRMU + Pegasus.

**Colab role:** actual training runs at scale; cognitive validation; distillation against teacher; Tier 10.6 deferred adoptions evaluated empirically.

**What 50M+50M validates:** infrastructure correctness, integration plumbing, Controller calibration, save/load fidelity, boundary enforcement, ratio regulation, metacognitive head wiring and gradient isolation, reflection trace pipeline mechanics. Everything mechanical.

**What 50M+50M does not validate:** cognitive performance, whether HM’s reflections add value over LM-alone, whether persistent state carries semantically useful structure, whether distillation produces a coding agent, whether the metacognitive head’s calibration generalizes to novel task distributions. These are parameter-count-bounded and require Colab-scale runs.

This split is honest and matches V3’s conclusion: “infrastructure is alive enough to calibrate; this is not proof that cognition works yet.”

